{
  "$comment": "Neutral shipped <sys/stat.h> (POSIX) — the FIRST real consumer of the plan-25 PER-TARGET struct `variants` mechanism. `struct stat` has a byte layout that DIVERGES per target: glibc x86-64-linux is 144 bytes (st_nlink is a 64-bit field at offset 16; st_mode at 24, after a 4-byte __pad0 that 8-aligns st_rdev), while glibc arm64-linux is 128 bytes (st_mode at 16, st_nlink a 32-bit field at 20; st_blksize is 32-bit with a __pad2). libc's fstat() writes the REAL struct and the program reads fields at OUR offsets, so a single layout would silently corrupt data on the other arch — the variant selector picks the field list matching (arch, format). The explicit padding fields (__pad0/__pad1/__pad2/reserved) make the layout engine's natural-alignment derivation reproduce the exact glibc offsets (sizeof = 144 / 128 respectively). The nested `struct timespec` (st_atim/mtim/ctim) is FLATTENED to its two i64 components (_sec/_nsec) here — bit-identical layout (timespec is {i64,i64}, 16 bytes); the real nested-timespec field names are a c14 authoring detail. Field types are RESOLVED hir-text builtins. c15c adds the macОS variant `when:{format:macho}` — the Darwin 64-bit-inode `struct stat` (verified against xnu/bsd/sys/stat.h): 144 bytes, the SAME SIZE as x86-64-linux but a COMPLETELY different layout (st_dev i32@0, st_mode/st_nlink uint16@4/6, st_ino u64@8, st_rdev i32@24 + a 4-byte __pad0@28 to 8-align FOUR timespecs incl. st_birthtimespec@80, st_blksize i32@112, the st_qspare tail) — the dangerous same-size swap the c13 lesson flagged (a size-only check would not catch it; the corpus pins a FIELD offset). arm64-macho and x86_64-macho are byte-identical (all fixed-width) so one `when:{format:macho}` covers both. The S_* constants + S_IS* macros + st_*time macros AGREE Linux↔macOS (the st_*tim_sec flat field names are shared). fstat/lstat/stat are the plain symbols (correct for arm64-macho, the macos-latest CI leg — the 64-bit-inode ABI; the x86_64-macho `$INODE64` asm-label alias is byte-pinned-only, no CI leg). Gated availableObjectFormats:[elf,macho]; a windows-pe `#include <sys/stat.h>` still fails loud (POSIX-on-windows = the separate os_win axis). RED-ON-DISABLE: neuter the variant selector (always variant 0) → the arm64-elf leg compiles the x86-64 144B layout (arm64 corpus sizeof==128 fails) AND the macho leg compiles the x86-64-elf field ORDER (the macho corpus's field-offset assertion fails).",
